# Jekyll Chirpy Website Structure and Capabilities

<rule>
name: jekyll_chirpy_structure
description: Defines the structure and capabilities of the Jekyll-based website using Chirpy theme

project_structure:
  core_directories:
    - _posts/: Blog posts in Markdown format
    - _layouts/: Template layouts for pages
    - _includes/: Reusable components
    - _sass/: SCSS styling files
    - assets/: Static files (images, js, css)
    - _data/: Site configuration data
    - _tabs/: Website main sections
    - _site/: Generated static site (not tracked)

styling_capabilities:
  - SCSS-based styling with modular structure
  - Dark/light theme support
  - Custom color schemes via _sass/colors/
  - Variables customization in _sass/variables-hook.scss

jekyll_features:
  - Static site generation
  - Blog post management with categories and tags
  - SEO optimization built-in
  - PWA support
  - Comments system (utterances/disqus/giscus)
  - TOC generation
  - Pagination
  - RSS feed
  - Sitemap generation
  - Google Analytics integration

theme_customization:
  - Configurable via _config.yml
  - Custom layouts in _layouts/
  - Component overrides in _includes/
  - Asset management in assets/
  - Custom JavaScript in _javascript/

content_creation:
  post_format: |
    ---
    title: Post Title
    date: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS +/-TTTT
    categories: [Category1, Category2]
    tags: [tag1, tag2]
    ---

best_practices:
  - Keep posts in _posts/ with YYYY-MM-DD-title.md format
  - Store images in assets/img/
  - Use _data/ for structured site data
  - Leverage _includes/ for reusable components
  - Override theme styles in _sass/
  - Configure site settings in _config.yml

metadata:
  version: 1.0
  theme: jekyll-theme-chirpy
  baseurl: ""
  url: "https://xallt.github.io"
</rule>